<SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar, Stocks Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar slipped marginally against the Japanese
yen Friday, while stock prices moved lower.
   The dollar closed at 143.53 yen, down 0.07 yen from Thursday's
close of 143.60. The U.S. currency started the day lower at 143.38
yen and ranged between 143.33 and 143.63 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which lost 106.73 points Thursday, fell 46.62 more
points, or 0.1 percent, to 34,739.93.
   Currency dealers said trading was light due to a lack of
market-affecting news.
   ``We can't make substantial dealings without strong
motivations,'' said a dealer at Daiichi Kangyo Bank, who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   Securities dealers said investors were cautious about trading
large volumes because of unstable political conditions.
   ``It is hard to recommend a customer buy shares on a day like
today, when a top Cabinet minister resigned,'' said Ichitaro
Watanabe, a dealer at Nikko Securities Co.
   Tokuo Yamashita, chief Cabinet secretary and top aide to Prime
Minister Toshiki Kaifu, resigned Friday after apologizing for an
extramarital affair with a bar hostess.
