<FILEID>AP-NR-08-25-89 0900EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--CrackRape     08-25 0143</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Crack Rape,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Sentenced for Raping Woman's Daughter as Payment for Crack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who sold crack cocaine to a woman in
exchange for letting him rape her 13-year-old daughter apologized
for the attack but was sentenced to 40 to 60 years in prison.
   Anthony Sawyer and Susan Barbier, both 29, were convicted earlier
on one count each of first-degree criminal sexual conduct. Sawyer
apologized at Thursday's sentencing.
   The victim, who now lives with her father, told Recorder's Court
Judge John Patrick O'Brien: ``The hour I spent with Anthony Sawyer
is the worst hour I have ever spent in my life.''
   Sawyer, 29, said he made the deal with Barbier because he was
addicted to crack. O'Brien, citing Sawyer's two previous rape
convictions, rejected that claim.
   Barbier, 29, faces sentencing Tuesday by Wayne County Circuit
Judge James Rashid.
</TEXT>
