<HEAD>Memorial Service For Those Killed in 1988 Ramstein Disaster</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RAMSTEIN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 450 U.S. military
personnel and their spouses filled a chapel Friday to remember the
70 people killed a year ago during an air show accident.
   ``The thoughts and prayers of the men and women of the U.S. Air
Forces in Europe are with those who lost loved ones or suffered
during the tragedy,'' said Gen. Michael J. Dugan, the head of the
