Kaiserslautern military community, placed a wreath at a stone marker
outside the chapel that is dedicated to the victims of last year's
disaster.
   The accident occurred on Aug. 28, 1988, when planes of an Italian
stunt-flying team collided over the air base, sending a jet engulfed
in flames plowing into the crowd. Four of the dead were Americans,
and 61 were West Germans. About 450 people were injured.
