   Geraldine Ferraro turns 54 on Saturday, but she's
got more important things to think about.
   ``I'm going to be the mother of the bride!,'' the former
Democratic vice presidential nominee told the Daily News.
   Her daughter, Donna, 27, will marry Paul Ullman on Oct. 14. The
two met at Salomon Bros., where both work.
   As for turning 54, Ferraro says: ``I feel better than I ever did.
I'm walking two miles a day on a treadmill. I've taken up golf. But
I'm getting a bit tired of lecturing. There's too much travel. So
I'm going to settle down right here and join a law firm in New York
in the next few months.
   ``For my birthday, I want a piece of jewelry from my husband to
wear at my daughter's wedding.''
