<FIRST>u i AM-SoccerBrawl     08-25 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Soccer Brawl,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>45 Injured In Soccer Brawl At Olympic Stadium</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soccer fans at Athens Olympic Stadium
attacked each other Friday night, then united against police who
tried to stop the melee. Police said 45 people were injured,
including 14 officers.
   A police spokesman said fans ripped out thousands of the
stadium's plastic seats and hurled them at each other or at officers.
   Fighting began late in a match between AEK of Athens and
Olympiakos of Piraeus, the top teams of last season, when they were
tied 2-2. Small scuffles had broken out each time a team scored.
   When the major battle began, the game was stopped and police
tried to disperse the belligerents with tear gas.
   The crowd turned on police and the violence spilled out of the
stadium. Two police motorcycles and nearly a dozen cars were
destroyed.
   Two policemen were hospitalized, but all others injured were
treated and released, according to the police spokesman. He said the
battle lasted about 1{ hours and no arrests were made.
