<FIRST>u i AM-Italy-Jews     08-25 0208</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Jews,0214</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jewish Emigres Fast In Front Of U.S. Embassy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of 12 Soviet Jews said Friday they are
fasting in front of the U.S. Embassy to protest being denied visas
to go to the United States.
   The U.S. government used to accept almost all Soviet Jews who
applied for immigration, but changed its policy in October because
of the large number now permitted to leave the Soviet Union.
   ``We have just been drinking water since Monday,'' said Edward
Leitman, who has lived for seven months with his wife and daughter
in Ladispoli, north of Rome. ``This may possibly make them change
their minds.''
   U.S. Embassy spokesman Michael Hahn declined comment on the
protest Friday. He said recently that Soviet Jews now must
demonstrate they were persecuted for political or religious reasons
to enter the United States as refugees.
   Since October, about 4,000 applicants at the embassy in Italy
have been denied visas, he said.
   The fast is the latest protest by Soviet Jews in front of the
embassy.
   Italy is a transit point for Soviets trying to immigrate to other
Western countries. All of the Jews could immigrate to Israel, but
most are trying to get to the United States or Canada.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
