<DOCNO> AP890825-0204 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-08-25-89 0313EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-TreasuryBills     08-25 0096</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Treasury Bills,0101</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rates on 52-Week Bills Rise in Auction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills rose
in Thursday's auction to the highest level since June.
   The Treasury Department sold $9.3 billion of the bills at an
average discount rate of 7.68 percent, up from 7.22 percent at the
last comparable auction on July 27.
   The rates were the highest since June 1, when the 1-year bills
sold for 8.18 percent.
   The new discount rate understates the actual return to investors
_ 8.27 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,223.50.
</TEXT>
