<FILEID>AP-NR-08-25-89 0205EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-AT&amp;T-GE-ABC     08-25 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AT&amp;T-GE-ABC,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>AT&amp;T Signs Satellite Deals With GE, ABC</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. says it has
chosen General Electric Co. to build its next generation of
communications satellites, and said ABC will use them to deliver
network television programming.
   The AT&amp;T contract with GE Astro-Space Division announced Thursday
has a potential value of more than $250 million. The amount AT&amp;T
will receive from ABC was not disclosed at the request of its
parent, Capital Cities-ABC Inc.
   GE will build three Telstar 4 satellites, and there is an option
for a fourth, AT&amp;T said. One will be launched in February 1993, one
will be launched in February 1994 and one will be a spare.
   ABC said it was the first television network to commit to buy
space on ``the next generation of satellites.''
</TEXT>
