   The Dow Jones industrial average jumped 56.53
points Thursday in its thirteenth-largest one-day point rise. Here
are the 15 best days for the average, including the percentage
change in value.
   Oct. 21, 1987 _ 186.84 to 2,027.85, 10.1 percent.
   Oct. 20, 1987 _ 102.27 to 1,841.01, 5.9 percent.
   Oct. 29, 1987 _ 91.51 to 1,938.33, 5.0 percent.
   Jan. 4, 1988 _ 76.42 to 2,015.25, 3.9 percent.
   Sept. 22, 1987 _ 75.23 to 2,568.05, 3.0 percent.
   May 31, 1988 _ 74.68 to 2,031.12, 3.8 percent.
   April 3, 1987 _ 69.89 to 2,390.34, 3.0 percent.
   April 21, 1987 _ 66.47 to 2,337.07, 2.9 percent.
   Dec. 14, 1987 _ 65.82 to 1,932.86, 3.5 percent.
   April 6, 1988 _ 64.16 to 2,061.67, 3.2 percent.
   Nov. 12, 1987 _ 61.01 to 1,960.21, 3.2 percent.
   May 12, 1989 _ 56.82 to 2,439.70, 2.4 percent.
   Aug. 24, 1989 _ 56.53 to 2,734.64, 2.1 percent.
   Dec. 8, 1987 _ 56.20 to 1,868.37, 3.1 percent.
   Oct. 30, 1987 _ 55.20 to 1,993.53, 2.8 percent.
