<HEAD>Time Warner To Merge Book Units</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Time Warner Inc. says it will combine book
publishing operations of the former Time Inc. and Warner
Communications Inc. in the first consolidation sparked by the merger
of the two media companies last month.
   The combination involves Little, Brown &amp; Co., a Time division
based in Boston, and Warner Books. Both publish for the consumer
markets.
   Time Warner said annual publishing revenues for the combined
operations would exceed $160 million this year.
